Description: Fragment of floor of Attic black-glazed pottery cup-skyphos. Fine fabric; underside modelled and glazed save for small central disc with dot and circle; large incised rosette at centre of floor, with band of incised double lines bounded by impressed tongues outside. Incised inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 581)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1534)
